hopobject.body: Wonderfull great site bestkenko.net If only those scenes made sense together. If only someone had said “uh, Dave, I’m not sure this ending is quite the right side of sane”. There is so much to admire in Beyond that it’s a real shame to see it squandered with such erratic plotting. Cage has often cited the need for video games to tap into more emotions than excitement. And Beyond, at times, genuinely does, even if it feels like a checklist. The game is at its best when it is at its most low-key, where Jodie has to deal with the burden of Aiden and the unwanted attention he brings her. A teenage house party turns nasty as Jodie takes her revenge on childish bullies. Later, Aiden tries to ruin a dinner date with disturbing jealousy.
